oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Spade Cooley Show - Hank Levine arrangements - 1954
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Excerpts from segments of the Spade Cooley Show, featuring Spade Cooley (host/performer), Kay Cee Jones (performer), and various other unidentified performers, broadcast in 1954. Musical arrangements by Hank Levine, according to tape case.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Spade Cooley; Kay Cee Jones
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:08) Spade Cooley introduces Kay Cee Jones -- (00:18) The Martins And The Coys (Kay Cee Jones) -- (02:13) Cooley thanks Jones -- (02:30) Cooley introduces the violin section to play a tune -- (02:58) [Unidentified tune] (band) -- (05:12) Cooley talks and introduces the next tune -- (05:26) Bluebells Of Scotland (Spade Cooley, band) -- (06:45) [Unidentified tune] (band) -- (07:35) Cooley talks and introduces and unidentified female vocalist -- (07:48) Oh By Jingo! ([Unidentified female vocalist]) -- (09:53) Cooley introduces Kay Cee Jones -- (10:00) You Can Always Tell A Texan, But You Can't Tell Him Very Much (Kay Cee Jones) -- (12:20) Kay Cee Jones and [Unidentified] ending -- (12:40) Cooley introduces the next tune -- (12:50) Lisbon Antigua (band) -- (15:30) Cooley introduces the next tune -- (15:37) Bye Bye Blackbird (various)
